WEBVTT

00:00.434 --> 00:04.370
<i> the people are represented</i>
<i> by two separate</i>

00:04.372 --> 00:05.905
<i> yet equally important groups:</i>

00:05.906 --> 00:07.439
<i> The police,</i>
<i> who investigate crime</i>

00:07.441 --> 00:10.309
<i> and the district attorneys,</i>
<i> who prosecute the offenders.</i>

00:10.311 --> 00:13.045
<i> These are their stories.</i>

00:16.584 --> 00:19.351
Please, Missus,
call the doctor.

00:19.353 --> 00:22.254
Cora, her temperature's down.

00:22.256 --> 00:23.288
She's not getting better.

00:23.290 --> 00:25.424
Waking her won't help.

00:25.426 --> 00:28.627
A doctor, an ambulance, 911--
you have to do something.

00:28.629 --> 00:30.229
You're being crazy.

00:30.231 --> 00:31.463
I want you to get your things.

00:31.465 --> 00:34.466
My husband
will send you a check.

00:34.468 --> 00:37.403
(<i> child wheezing lightly</i> )

00:39.106 --> 00:40.572
(<i> car horn honking</i> )

00:43.310 --> 00:46.512
Help, please! Help!

00:46.514 --> 00:50.482
Help! Help!

00:50.484 --> 00:53.118
Please, stop!

00:53.120 --> 00:55.354
What do you want,
honey?

00:55.356 --> 00:56.422
Mrs. Driscoll.

00:56.424 --> 00:57.823
Yes?

00:57.825 --> 00:59.591
I'm Officer Barton,
this is Officer Giordano.

00:59.593 --> 01:01.126
How are you doing?

01:01.128 --> 01:03.595
Your housekeeper says
you may have an emergency?

01:03.597 --> 01:06.298
Mrs. Amado
tends to overreact.

01:06.300 --> 01:07.299
Do you mind?

01:07.301 --> 01:08.434
Could we just come in

01:08.436 --> 01:09.535
and take a peek
at your daughter?

01:09.537 --> 01:11.370
That really isn't necessary.

01:11.372 --> 01:13.405
We'll just
be in and out.

01:13.407 --> 01:15.407
Excuse me, ma'am.

01:15.409 --> 01:18.177
She's been
a little feverish.

01:21.415 --> 01:22.381
(<i> wheezing</i> )

01:22.383 --> 01:24.249
Lady, this kid can't breathe.

01:24.251 --> 01:25.684
2-7 Charlie
to Central K.

01:25.686 --> 01:27.653
Go ahead, Charlie.
DISPATCHER:

01:27.655 --> 01:29.488
Did you call it in?

01:29.490 --> 01:32.257
Policy is firm:
only the chief resident-- me--

01:32.259 --> 01:33.358
can call the cops on parents.

01:33.360 --> 01:35.427
Listen, is this kid
going to make it?

01:35.429 --> 01:37.629
Strep, fever 105 plus--

01:37.631 --> 01:40.265
what kind of parent doesn't know
that's life-threatening?

01:40.267 --> 01:41.633
So, on the record, the
hospital's going to make

01:41.635 --> 01:43.168
a formal child
abuse complaint?

01:43.170 --> 01:45.204
Yes, neglect.

01:45.206 --> 01:46.405
You can't do this.

01:46.407 --> 01:48.373
I want to take
my daughter home.

01:48.375 --> 01:50.342
Ms. Driscoll, this is
Dr. Fisher, the chief resident.

01:50.344 --> 01:51.810
She won't authorize
a trach.

01:51.811 --> 01:53.277
And if I don't sign
an authorization,

01:53.280 --> 01:54.863
you can't treat her.

01:54.864 --> 01:56.447
This is Sergeant Cerreta
and Detective Logan.

01:56.450 --> 01:57.900
More policemen?

01:57.901 --> 01:59.351
You're not leaving us
any choice.

01:59.353 --> 02:01.320
You seem
like a reasonable woman.

02:01.322 --> 02:03.188
You want to tell us
what the problem is?

02:03.190 --> 02:04.389
Your husband here
tonight, ma'am?

02:04.391 --> 02:06.558
No, he's in Boston
on business.

02:06.560 --> 02:08.694
Well, you know, you understand
if the hospital

02:08.696 --> 02:12.297
files a formal complaint,
you could find yourself in jail.

02:12.299 --> 02:14.633
You can't force me
to let you operate.

02:14.635 --> 02:16.335
Are you serious?

02:16.337 --> 02:17.369
These people are trying

02:17.371 --> 02:19.171
to save your daughter's life.

02:19.173 --> 02:21.473
Right now, I am more concerned
about her soul.

02:21.475 --> 02:23.475
Mrs. Driscoll,
let us help Dinah.

02:23.477 --> 02:24.543
You can't help her.

02:24.545 --> 02:26.712
We don't believe
in modern medicine.

02:26.714 --> 02:28.614
You don't believe in it?

02:28.616 --> 02:31.450
Our religion forbids it.

02:31.452 --> 02:34.453
Code blue, E.R. Pediatrics.
WOMAN (<i> over PA system</i> ):

02:34.455 --> 02:36.722
Code blue, E.R. Pediatrics.

02:40.728 --> 02:42.394
MAN:
Excuse me, Miss.

02:42.396 --> 02:43.362
Step back.

02:43.364 --> 02:44.396
Get her intubated.

02:44.398 --> 02:45.631
1.8 milliliter epi.

02:45.633 --> 02:47.666
1/1,000 solution
I.V. push now.

02:47.668 --> 02:49.568
Let's get a central
line in here.

02:49.570 --> 02:51.270
Who's the pharmacist?

02:51.272 --> 02:53.238
WOMAN:
Now, now!

02:53.240 --> 02:56.775
Let's go
with 18 watts per second.

02:56.777 --> 02:57.943
WOMAN:
Level off.

02:57.945 --> 03:00.379
MAN:
Take the mask off.

03:00.381 --> 03:03.749
Clear.
(<i> sharp thud</i> )

03:03.751 --> 03:06.385
Still no pulse.

03:06.387 --> 03:08.420
Clear.

03:10.491 --> 03:11.557
Clear.

03:22.436 --> 03:25.204
She wasn't that sick!

03:41.222 --> 03:44.323
She wasn't that sick.

03:48.996 --> 03:53.298
